In this interview we discuss what appears to be the endgame for traditional=
 media companies as the streaming wars near their end. Topics include why Y=
ouTube is so well-positioned, the focus on churn mitigation, and why Netfli=
x's aggregator advantages are still underappreciated. We also use Netflix a=
s a lens to look at sports, before having a discussion about whether or not=
 AI is in a bubble, and end with a meta-discussion about how the analysis i=
ndustry is changing.

